name: Joann's Fabrics

comment: There's a women's restroom on the right side, but then there's a gender neutral bathroom on the left. Both are one stall bathrooms.

directions: It's in the hallway where they keep kittens

name: Joann fabrics

name: Vice & Versa
comment: 3 individual stalls, one with "Toilette" written on the door, the other two with only non gendered pictures

name: Nelson's Ice Cream

name: The Habanero

name: Bikes Not Bombs

name: Anytime Fitness

comment: The member entrance requires a keyfob, but the entrance on the right, by the offices, should be open during staffed hours.

name: Peninsula High School
directions:
At the bus turnaround there is a ramp down to the school. On the building next to the ramp there is a single door that leads to 3 classrooms: French, Photo/Graphic Design, and Broadcasting. In the Broadcasting room there is a gender neutral bathroom.

Also, inside the school in the main hall the nurse's office has a gender neutral bathroom that you can ask to use.
comment:
The bathroom in the Broadcasting room is only available to students after school. You also need to already be in there for something (sports, doing a radio show, etc). If you're an Underwriter or a parent, you don't need to be a student of PHS

The nurse's office you need to be a student.

name: Taco Bell
directions: Second floor by stairs

name: Shoppes at Grand Prairie
directions: Mall restrooms,  North and west of the central court,  across from Victoria's secret
comment: Family restroom with  lots of peeing options in one big lockable room. Never seen anyone else there.

name: UU Church
directions: In  the front door , right down the hallway.  Accessible single stall.
comment: Church is not always open, its a church. But lgbt friendly.

name: Jordan cleaning center
street: 128 S Lake St East Jordan, MI  49727 United States

name: Bamboo

name: Southern Hills Baptist Church
directions: Entrance to the right of the Welcome Center. Take the right past Hoskins Hall, then first left. Single-stall family restroom.

name: The Don CeSar
directions: Ground floor, by the Sea Porch restaurant. If entering by the ice cream parlor, walk down past the shops inside, make a right at the spiral staircase, and follow to the end of the hall. It will be down the short hallway on the right, on the rifht wall between the gendered bathrooms.
comment: The hotel is open to the public to shop and dine, you shouldn't have any issues using this bathroom.

name: Vic's Cafe
directions: Right at the back of the hallway
comment: You have to buy smth but the bathroom serves both the ice cream shop and the cafe so you could prob buy from either. (Or you might even go through the ice cream shop to the left and go into the cafe and they'll assume you're a customer of the ice cream shop and let you through.)

name: El Sombrero Taqueria

comment: Not sure if you have to be a paying customer but the food is great!

name: Pet Supplies Plus
directions: It's at the back left of the store, right next to the dog wash station. Drinking fountains are there too.
comment: We're all really nice, so I don't think anyone would care if you just came in for a restroom. If you still have anxiety about it, buy a bag of crickets, a dog biscuit, or donate a treat to the humane society at the register.

name: Trader Joe's
directions: Behind the greeting card section to the back right of the store

name: Leone's

name: Philter
